00:09.864 --> 00:11.622
Alan Shore!

00:13.562 --> 00:16.656
Alan! Where is Alan Shore?

00:16.656 --> 00:17.704
Alan Shore!

00:17.704 --> 00:19.607
–Hold her right there!
–The wedding gown.

00:19.647 --> 00:20.760
Alan Shore!

00:20.760 --> 00:22.939
Do you know Alan Shore?
Alan? Oh, no.

00:22.979 --> 00:25.575
Alan! Alan Shore!

00:25.916 --> 00:27.540
Alan!

00:27.540 --> 00:29.631
–Renatta…
–Okay, I know this looks really bad,

00:29.671 --> 00:31.404
but you have to believe me
I didn't do it.

00:31.444 --> 00:33.557
Please don't leave.
–Say nothing, Renatta.

00:33.597 --> 00:36.588
This woman is represented by council.
No interrogation. –Thank you, Alan.

00:36.628 --> 00:38.500
–I'll meet you in lockup. Okay?
–Okay. Okay, Alan.

00:38.540 --> 00:40.255
All right? It will be all right.

00:40.295 --> 00:41.947
You have the attorney.
Remain silent.

00:41.987 --> 00:43.207
Sir.

00:51.840 --> 00:53.592
Renatta…

00:53.981 --> 00:57.367
This is original even for you.

00:58.898 --> 01:00.726
I brought you a change of clothes.

01:00.766 --> 01:01.800
Ah, that's thoughtful.

01:01.840 --> 01:04.968
Actually, they need
the dress for evidence.

01:06.384 --> 01:07.858
So…

01:08.344 --> 01:10.286
tell me.

01:10.623 --> 01:11.968
From the start.

01:11.968 --> 01:15.719
Well, after you and I broke up,
I went back to my apartment.

01:15.759 --> 01:17.681
Skip ahead four or five years.

01:17.721 --> 01:20.620
Javier and I met at the opera.

01:20.620 --> 01:24.550
It was Strauss' ‘Die Fledermaus’.

01:24.550 --> 01:28.146
I was sitting in front of him,
he started playing with my hair.

01:28.186 --> 01:32.518
From there it was pretty much
a straight line to the engagement.

01:32.518 --> 01:35.231
Would you like me to look away?

01:35.231 --> 01:38.382
Yeah, if you have
to sneeze or something.

01:38.382 --> 01:41.945
We opted for a courthouse
wedding because…

01:41.945 --> 01:44.807
well, who needs a big fuss?
Besides I thought it was fitting.

01:44.847 --> 01:47.458
You know how much I love the law.

01:47.458 --> 01:49.037
We arrived.

01:49.037 --> 01:53.468
Waited for a bit in the corridor
with the other happy couples.

01:53.468 --> 01:57.189
I believe they need everything.

01:57.189 --> 01:59.190
The clerk showed us to a waiting room

01:59.230 --> 02:02.400
where we get ready for a few
minutes before the ceremony.

02:02.440 --> 02:06.808
Then he left to take another
couple to the judge's chambers.

02:06.808 --> 02:09.443
We necked for a bit.

02:09.443 --> 02:13.490
Then I began to feel weak.

02:13.490 --> 02:19.853
This corset was cutting off
my circulation. I…

02:20.507 --> 02:21.927
I fainted.

02:21.927 --> 02:26.630
When I came to, there he was
lying in a pool of blood.

02:26.630 --> 02:32.814
His own ice-tempered beveled edge stainless
steel scissors sticking out of his chest.

02:32.814 --> 02:35.160
He was a wig maker.
–Of course.

02:35.160 --> 02:37.858
He takes scissors with him everywhere.

02:37.858 --> 02:41.876
He was talking about giving me
a trim before the ceremony.

02:41.876 --> 02:43.962
He was always at me
with those scissors.

02:44.002 --> 02:46.672
You can see how bouncy my ends are.

02:46.672 --> 02:52.375
I've pulled out the shears
hoping to save him but…

02:54.146 --> 02:56.447
nothing.

02:56.447 --> 02:59.213
He was dead.

02:59.942 --> 03:02.355
Renatta…

03:03.845 --> 03:06.243
I have missed you.

